\section{Introduction}

The key idea is to \emph{desugar} the source verse
programs into a core language that is \vcshort (the ICFP23 calculus)
extended with
%
(1) \emph{syntax} to record \emph{assumptions} and \emph{obligations},
%
(2) \emph{rewrite rules} that use the assumptions to discharge obligations.
%
The job of the verifier is to \emph{rewrite} the (desugared)
term using \emph{all} the rules, that is, the ICFP23 rules \emph{and}
the new verification rules, until no obligations remain, at which point
the term is deemed verified.

Next, we describe the extensions to the syntax \cref{sec:syntax},
explain the desugaring by means of examples \cref{sec:desugaring},
present the verification rewrite rules \cref{sec:verification}, and
finally show a few examples that show how the verifier works from
end-to-end.

